         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne bot. Garden ¶ 25/5/70 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ In accordance with your instructions ¶ See W. Odgers to M, 21 May 1870, in this edition as 70-05-21a. ¶  ¶ I forwarded the memorandum respecting an article i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.05.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James McCulloch</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">V70/5693, unit 465, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne bot. Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">25/5/70</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In accordance with your instructions<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See W. Odgers to M, 21 May 1870, in this edition as 70-05-21a.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I forwarded the memorandum respecting an article in the Argus, to the Inspector of forests and have now the honor to send a letter, supposed to contain his answer, the contents of the letter being unknown to me.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your obed.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Director of the botan Garden.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The hon the Chief Secretary.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Under Secretary, W. Odgers, returned Ferguson's letter to M on 31 May 1870 with the following instruction: 'Mr Fergusson's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[i.e. William Ferguson]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reply to the Chief Secretary's inquiry must be sent in the usual official way viz through Dr. Mueller and open and in any communication he desires to address to me on public business he will be good enough to adopt my official title of Under Secretary. Dr Mueller will so inform him.' M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>minuted<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 1 June: 'Minute of the Undersecretary submitted for perusal to the Inspector of forests and for his information. Letter herewith returned.'</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>W. Odgers, 1 June 1870; note 2 includes Ferguson's response to ther minute.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
